##! Please refer to the documentation at
##! https://coreruleset.org/docs/development/regex_assembly/.
##!
##! Rule 943120: Session Fixation - SessionID Parameter Name with No Referer
##!
##! Description: Detects common session ID parameter names used in
##! session fixation attacks when no Referer header is present.
##! Chained with a check for missing Referer header.
##!
##! Note: This rule uses t:lowercase transformation, so all patterns
##! are in lowercase.
##!
##! Note: Rule 943110 has a superset of these session names.
##! A shared include could be created in a future refactor.
##!^ ^
##!$ $

##! Java/J2EE Session IDs
jsessionid
jservsession
jwsession

##! ASP/ASP.NET Session IDs
aspsessionid
asp\.net_sessionid

##! PHP Session IDs
phpsession
phpsessid

##! Oracle WebLogic
weblogicsession

##! Generic Session IDs
session_id
session-id
sessionid
_session_id

##! ColdFusion Session IDs
cfid
cftoken
cfsid

##! Python/Flask
_flask_session

##! Node.js / Express
connect\.sid

##! Laravel
laravel_session
